| Missing scenario | Why it matters |
|---|---|
| Bang-only with no terms (`!w`) | `prefix[2]` is undefined → `term` should be `''` |
| Special characters in terms (`!w C++ operator`) | `encodeURIComponent` must handle `+`, `#`, `&` |
| Bang with multiple spaces between tokens | Whitespace normalisation |
| Unknown bang in suffix form (`cats !zzz`) | Symmetry with prefix unknown-bang test |

```ts
it('handles a bang with no search terms', () => {
  expect(resolveBang('!w')?.redirectUrl).toBe(
    'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:Search?search='
  );
});

it('encodes special characters in terms', () => {
  const url = resolveBang('!w C++ operators')?.redirectUrl;
  expect(url).toContain('C%2B%2B');
});

it('returns null for an unknown bang in suffix form', () => {
  expect(resolveBang('cats !zzz')).toBeNull();
});
```

| Missing scenario | Why it matters |
|---|---|
| Query below `MIN_SEARCH_QUERY_LENGTH` | No test for lower bound (currently tested implicitly via empty string, but `''` → trimmed → 0 chars; `MIN_SEARCH_QUERY_LENGTH = 1`) |
| URL with `#fragment` | `formatDisplayUrl` — fragment should be stripped (it is, via `url.search` not including hash) |
| URL with port | `example.com:8080/path` — host includes port |
| Control characters stripped | `normalizeSearchQuery` strips `\x00-\x1f` per the regex |

```ts
it('strips URL fragments', () => {
  expect(formatDisplayUrl('https://example.com/page#section')).toBe('example.com/page');
});

it('preserves port in URL host', () => {
  expect(formatDisplayUrl('http://localhost:3000/api')).toBe('localhost:3000/api');
});

it('normalizes control characters as spaces', () => {
  expect(normalizeSearchQuery('hello\x00world')).toBe('hello world');
});
```

| Missing scenario | Why it matters |
|---|---|
| Fractional interval (< 1 full interval elapsed) | `Math.floor` must not refill yet |
| `retryAfterSeconds` is at least 1 | Contract states `Math.max(1, …)` — not explicitly asserted |
| Capacity is exactly restored (not exceeded) after many intervals | Already partially tested but worth an exact assertion |

```ts
it('does not refill for less than one full interval', () => {
  const drained: TokenBucketState = { tokens: 0, lastRefillAt: 0, updatedAt: 0 };
  const decision = consumeTokenBucket(drained, OPTIONS, OPTIONS.refillIntervalMs - 1);
  expect(decision.allowed).toBe(false);
});

it('retryAfterSeconds is at least 1', () => {
  let state: TokenBucketState | undefined;
  for (let i = 0; i < OPTIONS.capacity; i++) {
    ({ state } = consumeTokenBucket(state, OPTIONS, 0));
  }
  const blocked = consumeTokenBucket(state, OPTIONS, 0);
  expect(blocked.retryAfterSeconds).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(1);
});
```

